article.headline: Jackson State 89, Alcorn State 67
article.story: JACKSON, Miss. (AP) -- Trey Johnson had 19 points to lead Jackson State to an 89-67 victory over Alcorn State on Saturday night. The Tigers (11-11, 7-3 Southwestern Athletic Conference) overcame a 26-point performance by Alcorn State's Delvin Thompson, using a 29-4 run late in the first half to take the lead for good in their third straight victory. Johnson had eight of his 11 first-half points during the run, which gave Jackson State a 36-22 lead with 2:42 left before halftime. Alcorn State closed to 43-36 with 16 minutes to play, but Jackson State shot 57 percent in the second half and cruised from there. Julius Young had 12 points and Antonio Williams-Parker added 10 for the Tigers. The Braves (4-6, 4-15) have lost two straight and six of their last seven. Juan Wyatt added 14 points for Alcorn State, which shot 35 percent.
